1
00:00:00,427 --> 00:00:03,006
I remember everything now, Dad.

2
00:00:03,006 --> 00:00:05,973
Mom didn't want to leave us.

3
00:00:05,973 --> 00:00:08,460
She did that to protect me.

4
00:00:10,947 --> 00:00:16,186
When Sun remembered everything
and accepted all that happened,

5
00:00:16,966 --> 00:00:20,160
I could feel that he'd finally let it go.

6
00:00:21,299 --> 00:00:24,940
Little Sun and I don't have to
switch every other day anymore.

7
00:00:29,473 --> 00:00:31,200
Someone once told me

8
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,520
[Teaching License Examination: Session 1]
that life is like a storybook,

9
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:40,080
because it's full of problems and obstacles.

10
00:00:40,953 --> 00:00:45,340
Some moments may not look pretty.

11
00:00:45,340 --> 00:00:49,473
It might seem tiring and difficult,

12
00:00:49,473 --> 00:00:52,273
to the point where you just want to
get away from it as soon as possible.

13
00:00:59,439 --> 00:01:02,047
- But there's one teacher...
- Pobmek!

14
00:01:02,047 --> 00:01:07,493
Who taught me
that if life had no problems at all,

15
00:01:07,493 --> 00:01:10,086
we'd never discover anything new,

16
00:01:10,826 --> 00:01:14,080
or dare to do the things
we never thought we could.

17
00:01:16,026 --> 00:01:17,186
Surprise!

18
00:01:17,186 --> 00:01:18,280
[We're Rooting For You]
[Teacher Pobmek Is The Best]

19
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:22,253
I brought the kids to cheer you on
in person, Teacher Pobmek.

20
00:01:22,253 --> 00:01:24,720
How was it? Did you do okay?

21
00:01:30,719 --> 00:01:32,245
Of course I did.

22
00:01:32,245 --> 00:01:34,258
Yay!

23
00:01:34,258 --> 00:01:35,944
If we never faced any problems in life,

24
00:01:35,944 --> 00:01:37,664
we'd probably never realize

25
00:01:37,664 --> 00:01:39,900
-who's willing to stand by our side
-Teacher Pobmek!

26
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:41,473
On our worst days.

27
00:01:41,473 --> 00:01:46,390
And we'd probably never know
what happiness looks like.

28
00:01:46,390 --> 00:01:48,246
Teacher Solar.

29
00:01:48,246 --> 00:01:51,846
There was one question
I wasn't very sure about.

30
00:01:52,707 --> 00:01:54,498
Can I get your advice?

31
00:01:54,498 --> 00:01:56,277
Wow.

32
00:01:56,277 --> 00:01:58,170
This teacher's really fired up.

33
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:00,665
Of course.

34
00:02:00,665 --> 00:02:02,640
Which question do you want to ask about?

35
00:02:20,066 --> 00:02:26,305
There was this question about
children's physical development.

36
00:02:26,305 --> 00:02:29,957
Which muscle group develops first?

37
00:02:31,383 --> 00:02:33,602
The large muscles.

38
00:02:33,602 --> 00:02:36,457
Children can stand
before they can grab things.

39
00:02:37,978 --> 00:02:39,778
Got it.

40
00:02:43,016 --> 00:02:45,780
And when do children learn about sharing?

41
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:47,497
Come on, Teacher!

42
00:02:47,497 --> 00:02:49,393
Stop being so curious.

43
00:02:49,393 --> 00:02:51,764
Focus on the homework in front of you.

44
00:02:52,550 --> 00:02:57,712
It's kinda hard to do homework here, Teacher.

45
00:03:02,562 --> 00:03:06,674
Homework is supposed to be done on a desk.

46
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:17,040
[Today Is A Good Day]

47
00:04:35,396 --> 00:04:36,783
Who is this for?

48
00:04:37,664 --> 00:04:40,565
It's for you, kid. Obviously.

49
00:04:43,291 --> 00:04:45,185
You mean Sun?

50
00:04:50,752 --> 00:04:52,552
Oh, right.

51
00:04:53,755 --> 00:04:55,555
I forgot.

52
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:58,861
I've gotten so used to doing this.

53
00:05:13,129 --> 00:05:15,080
I can feel that...

54
00:05:16,909 --> 00:05:19,640
Sun has fallen into a very deep sleep.

55
00:05:20,658 --> 00:05:22,586
He's probably not going to wake up again.

56
00:05:34,596 --> 00:05:38,073
Then I guess we should put those things away.

57
00:05:56,378 --> 00:05:57,700
Did Sun want to go to the beach?

58
00:05:57,700 --> 00:05:58,980
Yeah.

59
00:05:59,923 --> 00:06:02,824
He asked me to take him there
when we did the class play.

60
00:06:03,965 --> 00:06:05,808
You even signed off on it.

61
00:06:07,202 --> 00:06:09,240
I guess we have to go.

62
00:06:11,967 --> 00:06:13,075
Okay.

63
00:06:13,075 --> 00:06:16,361
We can celebrate your special day too.

64
00:06:16,361 --> 00:06:19,337
You're late! You're late! You're late!

65
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:21,763
Today's a special day too.

66
00:06:21,763 --> 00:06:23,324
Let's go.

67
00:06:23,324 --> 00:06:24,747
We don't want to be late.

68
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:34,595
- Hi.
- Hello.

69
00:06:34,595 --> 00:06:35,915
Your child graduated.

70
00:06:35,915 --> 00:06:37,715
Hi.

71
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:40,460
Congratulations.

72
00:06:47,868 --> 00:06:50,188
Four, what's wrong?

73
00:06:50,188 --> 00:06:51,539
Your dad didn't come?

74
00:06:51,539 --> 00:06:52,824
He did.

75
00:06:52,824 --> 00:06:55,819
Oh? Then why are you crying?

76
00:06:55,819 --> 00:06:58,835
Because you gave me an A in math.

77
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:01,280
My dad's going to be so happy.

78
00:07:04,668 --> 00:07:06,360
Of course, I gave you an A.

79
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:09,541
You turned in all your homework
and aced your exam.

80
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:11,215
Why wouldn't I?

81
00:07:12,929 --> 00:07:15,590
Now that's a real man.

82
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:17,794
[Report Book]
Yes, yes.

83
00:07:17,794 --> 00:07:21,951
Good job for having the courage
to show your feelings.

84
00:07:21,951 --> 00:07:25,125
We're all human.

85
00:07:25,125 --> 00:07:27,287
Whether we're kids or adults,

86
00:07:27,287 --> 00:07:30,364
it's okay to cry if we want to.

87
00:07:31,193 --> 00:07:34,426
Tinker Bell, you talked a lot.

88
00:07:34,426 --> 00:07:39,160
That's character development.

89
00:07:39,844 --> 00:07:41,841
Wow!

90
00:07:41,841 --> 00:07:43,909
You all got together so early this morning.

91
00:07:43,909 --> 00:07:46,280
Did something good happen?

92
00:07:50,689 --> 00:07:54,483
Sorry, Teacher.

93
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,645
I ironed this so nicely, you know?

94
00:08:00,417 --> 00:08:04,039
Teacher Jee, aren't you the emcee for today?

95
00:08:04,039 --> 00:08:05,826
Do you have a spare outfit?

96
00:08:05,826 --> 00:08:07,622
No, I don't.

97
00:08:08,901 --> 00:08:10,253
Come on.

98
00:08:10,253 --> 00:08:11,953
I'll help you out, buddy.

99
00:08:11,953 --> 00:08:13,366
Let's go.

100
00:08:15,895 --> 00:08:19,543
Wow! PobmekJee is back!

101
00:08:19,543 --> 00:08:20,986
It's JeePobmek.

102
00:08:20,986 --> 00:08:22,236
Gotta switch things up.

103
00:08:22,236 --> 00:08:25,405
That's a bit weird, but interesting.

104
00:08:25,405 --> 00:08:29,265
What do you girls think
Teacher Sataporn would say?

105
00:08:30,446 --> 00:08:32,558
It can only be PobmekSolar.

106
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,736
Come on. The event is about to start.

107
00:08:36,954 --> 00:08:38,361
Let's go.

108
00:08:47,339 --> 00:08:48,762
Hey, Pobmek.

109
00:08:49,822 --> 00:08:53,320
Can we swap shirts?

110
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:58,739
I really can't announce the students' names
on stage looking like this.

111
00:08:58,739 --> 00:09:00,638
We can't.

112
00:09:00,638 --> 00:09:02,625
Do you want to just take it off?

113
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:05,712
You're the P.E. teacher.
Just play a bodybuilder.

114
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:07,326
Are you crazy?

115
00:09:07,326 --> 00:09:09,440
This is an elementary school.

116
00:09:14,682 --> 00:09:16,638
It won't come off.

117
00:09:22,274 --> 00:09:23,967
Hey, Jee.

118
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:25,960
I think you should wear this.

119
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:32,520
[Congratulations]

120
00:09:33,085 --> 00:09:34,461
Hello.

121
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:37,227
Please come in.

122
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,051
Hello, ma'am.

123
00:09:39,051 --> 00:09:40,633
This way, please.

124
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,466
Please come in.

125
00:09:43,973 --> 00:09:46,190
Hello.

126
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:49,316
Excuse me, have you seen Miss Fresh?

127
00:09:49,316 --> 00:09:50,726
Miss Fresh?

128
00:09:50,726 --> 00:09:52,774
You mean...

129
00:09:53,823 --> 00:09:55,131
It's just as chaotic as ever!

130
00:09:55,131 --> 00:09:59,063
You know, one parent asked for a seat
with a built-in full body massage.

131
00:09:59,063 --> 00:10:00,349
Is that even reasonable?

132
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:02,629
Not at all.

133
00:10:02,629 --> 00:10:04,857
Right, sir?

134
00:10:04,857 --> 00:10:06,390
Oh!

135
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:07,894
Principal Maximoff.

136
00:10:07,894 --> 00:10:11,174
Long time no see, Miss Fresh.

137
00:10:12,375 --> 00:10:13,946
Hello.

138
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,463
Hello, Principal Maximoff.

139
00:10:15,463 --> 00:10:17,457
- You're back from your trip?
- Yes.

140
00:10:17,457 --> 00:10:20,430
My spiritual journey has ended.

141
00:10:20,430 --> 00:10:25,040
I'm ready to be the principal again.

142
00:10:27,481 --> 00:10:30,535
Can I find a seat inside?

143
00:10:30,535 --> 00:10:33,164
Teacher Solar will take you.

144
00:10:33,164 --> 00:10:34,820
Solar, can you help me out?

145
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:36,074
Okay.

146
00:10:36,074 --> 00:10:37,304
This way, please.

147
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:39,104
Thank you.

148
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:49,120
Have you been here long?

149
00:11:02,991 --> 00:11:04,749
Are you okay?

150
00:11:04,749 --> 00:11:06,180
Ready?

151
00:11:31,588 --> 00:11:35,935
Hello, students and parents.

152
00:11:35,935 --> 00:11:41,286
Today is an important day
for the children as they grow

153
00:11:41,286 --> 00:11:45,840
and prepare to move on to the next grade
in the coming academic year.

154
00:11:47,934 --> 00:11:53,623
And today will probably be my last day

155
00:11:53,623 --> 00:11:57,476
serving as acting principal.

156
00:12:11,155 --> 00:12:17,640
Honestly, at first,
I didn't want to be principal at all.

157
00:12:18,354 --> 00:12:23,560
And I actually feel like
I'm still not even doing a good job.

158
00:12:24,753 --> 00:12:26,593
But at least,

159
00:12:28,191 --> 00:12:34,960
I've learned so many new things
from the children,

160
00:12:38,001 --> 00:12:40,320
the teachers,

161
00:12:43,139 --> 00:12:46,360
and the parents as well.

162
00:12:49,704 --> 00:12:52,973
Even though it was only for a short time,

163
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:56,878
this semester

164
00:12:58,119 --> 00:13:02,440
has been the best time of my life.

165
00:13:05,043 --> 00:13:11,930
Thank you all so much. Truly.

166
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:47,200
Teacher Sodchuen!

167
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,520
Alright, alright.

168
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:51,919
Thank you all so much.

169
00:13:51,919 --> 00:13:57,050
Next, I'd like to invite Principal Maximoff

170
00:13:57,050 --> 00:14:01,068
to come up and say a few words
to the children today.

171
00:14:18,934 --> 00:14:21,611
Principal Maximoff, are you okay?

172
00:14:21,611 --> 00:14:29,392
I'm so moved by the speech
you gave everyone, Miss Fresh.

173
00:14:29,392 --> 00:14:36,680
I realized I made the right decision
making you principal.

174
00:14:41,150 --> 00:14:45,042
So from now on,

175
00:14:45,042 --> 00:14:50,610
Miss Fresh will step up as principal,

176
00:14:50,610 --> 00:14:55,692
officially taking over.

177
00:14:55,692 --> 00:14:56,959
Wait.

178
00:14:56,959 --> 00:14:58,411
What?

179
00:15:04,452 --> 00:15:11,901
Principal Sodchuen!

180
00:15:16,758 --> 00:15:18,558
Nice, Wai.

181
00:15:19,622 --> 00:15:21,422
Here.

182
00:15:28,454 --> 00:15:30,138
Did you really have to be this extra?

183
00:15:30,945 --> 00:15:32,745
Of course.

184
00:15:41,856 --> 00:15:47,440
Alright. Up next, please welcome Teacher Jee!

185
00:16:03,690 --> 00:16:07,546
Next, we'll be presenting certificates

186
00:16:07,546 --> 00:16:10,051
to the student receiving
the Best Friendship of the Year award.

187
00:16:10,051 --> 00:16:15,777
And this year,
we also have a Teacher of the Year award.

188
00:16:15,777 --> 00:16:19,720
They were selected through votes
from students across the entire school.

189
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:25,763
And the winners

190
00:16:25,763 --> 00:16:28,740
of this year's Best Friendship
and Teacher of the Year awards

191
00:16:28,740 --> 00:16:30,540
are...

192
00:16:35,531 --> 00:16:38,960
Little Sun and Teacher Solar!

193
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:55,165
Teacher Solar!

194
00:17:07,912 --> 00:17:12,538
Thank you for all the votes
for Little Sun and me.

195
00:17:12,538 --> 00:17:15,018
I'm so happy for him.

196
00:17:17,176 --> 00:17:20,600
Even though he doesn't
come to school anymore,

197
00:17:21,390 --> 00:17:23,577
everyone still misses him.

198
00:17:28,024 --> 00:17:31,266
This past year has been really tough for me,

199
00:17:32,353 --> 00:17:36,960
but I made it through
because of the lovely kids,

200
00:17:38,674 --> 00:17:40,760
the understanding parents,

201
00:17:42,162 --> 00:17:46,880
and the teachers who have been
cheering me on and staying by my side.

202
00:17:50,491 --> 00:17:52,520
Especially Teacher Pobmek.

203
00:17:54,704 --> 00:17:56,504
Thank you.

204
00:18:03,410 --> 00:18:09,240
[Teaching License - Pobmek, Solar]

205
00:18:35,681 --> 00:18:38,549
- What are you doing?
- Shit! You scared me!

206
00:18:38,549 --> 00:18:41,663
Serves you right for acting all suspicious.

207
00:18:42,837 --> 00:18:44,762
Planning to surprise me?

208
00:18:44,762 --> 00:18:46,397
Yeah.

209
00:18:46,397 --> 00:18:48,560
But it's not a surprise anymore.

210
00:18:50,826 --> 00:18:52,408
You can go back to sleep.

211
00:18:52,408 --> 00:18:54,149
I'll wake you up when it's ready.

212
00:18:55,405 --> 00:18:56,782
Okay.

213
00:19:08,052 --> 00:19:11,291
Hey, why aren't you going to sleep?

214
00:19:11,291 --> 00:19:13,363
I changed my mind.

215
00:19:13,363 --> 00:19:17,375
I'm going to help you, so you won't be tired.

216
00:19:17,375 --> 00:19:19,318
Save your energy for something else.

217
00:19:21,102 --> 00:19:25,447
I always have the energy to do that for you.

218
00:19:27,721 --> 00:19:29,928
Why are you making pancakes again?

219
00:19:33,776 --> 00:19:35,489
You ask a lot.

220
00:19:35,489 --> 00:19:38,315
You keep asking.

221
00:19:38,315 --> 00:19:41,285
- You're not really not going to tell me?
- No.

222
00:19:48,617 --> 00:19:51,572
Seriously? You had to go that far?

223
00:19:59,201 --> 00:20:01,132
Fine, I'll tell you.

224
00:20:25,937 --> 00:20:34,221
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

225
00:20:34,221 --> 00:20:39,968
♪ Happy birthday ♪

226
00:20:39,968 --> 00:20:46,280
♪ Happy birthday, Solar ♪

227
00:20:55,631 --> 00:21:00,360
I chose to make pancakes because...

228
00:21:02,882 --> 00:21:05,415
I thought you and Sun would both like them.

229
00:21:07,479 --> 00:21:08,893
Yeah.

230
00:21:10,222 --> 00:21:12,284
I think Sun would love them so much.

231
00:21:41,643 --> 00:21:43,532
I'll do the navigation.

232
00:21:46,502 --> 00:21:49,518
No need. I'll handle it.

233
00:21:49,518 --> 00:21:50,992
We're going to the beach today.

234
00:21:50,992 --> 00:21:54,528
If you give directions,
we'll probably end up in the mountains.

235
00:21:54,528 --> 00:21:56,703
Oh, come on!

236
00:21:56,703 --> 00:21:58,324
You really don't trust me that much?

237
00:21:58,324 --> 00:21:59,962
It's not that I don't trust you,

238
00:21:59,962 --> 00:22:03,359
but you don't have to be good at everything.

239
00:22:03,359 --> 00:22:05,759
Alright, little bro?

240
00:22:07,623 --> 00:22:10,372
Okay. Go ahead, big bro.

241
00:22:10,372 --> 00:22:12,109
I'll take a nap then.

242
00:22:12,109 --> 00:22:14,518
Make yourself comfortable, young master.

243
00:22:25,792 --> 00:22:30,480
It's a shame...
that Sun couldn't come with us.

244
00:22:40,350 --> 00:22:43,100
We're finally keeping the promise to him.

245
00:22:55,782 --> 00:22:58,100
Let's go before the traffic gets bad.

246
00:23:23,036 --> 00:23:24,570
Solar.

247
00:23:25,961 --> 00:23:27,430
Solar.

248
00:23:29,653 --> 00:23:31,101
Solar.

249
00:23:43,537 --> 00:23:45,080
Sun.

250
00:24:05,123 --> 00:24:06,966
Have we arrived?

251
00:24:10,873 --> 00:24:12,252
Yeah.

252
00:24:12,252 --> 00:24:13,858
We've arrived.

253
00:24:13,858 --> 00:24:14,940
Let's go.

254
00:24:14,940 --> 00:24:16,490
Okay.

255
00:24:58,927 --> 00:25:06,034
If Sun came to the beach,
what do you think he'd do first?

256
00:25:33,637 --> 00:25:38,360
I think he'd jump straight into the water.

257
00:25:42,644 --> 00:25:44,866
You're right.

258
00:25:44,866 --> 00:25:47,092
And you?

259
00:25:47,092 --> 00:25:49,162
What do you want to do first?

260
00:25:53,415 --> 00:25:55,215
I guess...

261
00:25:58,545 --> 00:26:00,458
I want to play in the water

262
00:26:02,634 --> 00:26:06,153
with both you and Sun.

263
00:26:10,854 --> 00:26:12,107
Hey! What are you doing?

264
00:26:12,107 --> 00:26:14,651
- Taking you to play in the water!
- Solar!

265
00:26:22,917 --> 00:26:24,467
What are you even doing?

266
00:26:24,467 --> 00:26:26,520
Solar!

267
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:28,740
I brought you into the water to play.

268
00:26:29,433 --> 00:26:32,068
Well? Satisfied now?

269
00:26:32,068 --> 00:26:33,868
Very.

270
00:26:36,093 --> 00:26:38,283
You said you wanted to play
with Little Sun, right?

271
00:26:39,379 --> 00:26:41,033
Try copying me.

272
00:26:41,982 --> 00:26:43,182
Copy you?

273
00:26:43,182 --> 00:26:44,633
Yeah.

274
00:26:44,633 --> 00:26:46,480
Try closing your eyes.

275
00:26:47,730 --> 00:26:48,760
Come on, close your eyes.

276
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:50,316
Okay.

277
00:26:50,316 --> 00:26:52,649
Remember the moment we first arrived?

278
00:26:52,649 --> 00:26:53,772
Yeah.

279
00:26:53,772 --> 00:26:56,091
What did you say you wanted to do?

280
00:26:56,091 --> 00:26:58,251
Try imagining it.

281
00:27:14,749 --> 00:27:16,348
Hey!

282
00:27:43,751 --> 00:27:49,114
Little Sun,
even though we never met in person,

283
00:27:49,114 --> 00:27:54,161
I've always known and felt your presence
all this time.

284
00:27:56,179 --> 00:28:01,840
Ever since you came into my life,
I've learned so much.

285
00:28:12,533 --> 00:28:15,786
Back then, you must've been hurting,

286
00:28:15,786 --> 00:28:18,961
fragile, and confused,

287
00:28:18,961 --> 00:28:21,066
to the point where you ended up
punishing yourself,

288
00:28:21,066 --> 00:28:23,840
thinking you didn't deserve love from anyone.

289
00:28:24,687 --> 00:28:26,371
But listen to me.

290
00:28:26,371 --> 00:28:29,355
You've always been a good kid.

291
00:28:29,355 --> 00:28:31,680
You did nothing wrong.

292
00:28:32,761 --> 00:28:36,876
There's nothing to blame yourself for,
or be afraid of anymore.

293
00:28:38,239 --> 00:28:42,367
You've always been a light
to the people around you.

294
00:28:42,367 --> 00:28:46,720
You're like sunshine
that brings warmth and brightness.

295
00:28:48,588 --> 00:28:54,126
You're worthy of a good love,
just like everyone else.

296
00:28:54,126 --> 00:28:56,520
Trust me, Little Sun.

297
00:29:08,900 --> 00:29:10,167
Pobmek.

298
00:29:13,422 --> 00:29:14,730
What is it?

299
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:25,824
No. It's nothing.

300
00:29:28,444 --> 00:29:30,255
There is something.

301
00:29:31,115 --> 00:29:34,278
Fine. There is.

302
00:29:46,408 --> 00:29:48,272
Thank you so much

303
00:29:49,700 --> 00:29:54,020
for bringing Sun and me to the beach
like you promised.

304
00:30:11,082 --> 00:30:12,465
Pobmek.

305
00:30:19,326 --> 00:30:21,640
Can I ask you for something?

306
00:30:23,156 --> 00:30:24,653
What now?

307
00:30:29,715 --> 00:30:37,073
Can you play that song... for me again?

308
00:30:49,784 --> 00:30:55,857
This will probably... be the last time.

309
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:06,840
[Talent Stage]

310
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:12,685
Bomb!

311
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:16,497
You're still as hyped up as ever, huh?

312
00:32:19,333 --> 00:32:21,603
Let's hug!

313
00:32:24,350 --> 00:32:25,785
My name is Sun.

314
00:32:25,785 --> 00:32:28,985
I'm 7 years old, in Grade 2 Class 1.

315
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:40,040
[I'm sorry I made you sick, Uncle]
At least Sun stopped calling you Kidnapper.

316
00:32:43,159 --> 00:32:44,738
Solar!

317
00:34:32,602 --> 00:34:34,763
Don't be sad.

318
00:34:36,980 --> 00:34:39,200
Sun is not really gone.

319
00:34:50,639 --> 00:34:52,439
Sun is me.

320
00:34:54,590 --> 00:34:56,390
I am Sun.

321
00:34:58,547 --> 00:35:01,147
We're a part of each other.

322
00:35:02,193 --> 00:35:03,579
So...

323
00:35:04,998 --> 00:35:07,250
he'll stay with us forever.

324
00:35:14,870 --> 00:35:16,477
In here.

325
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:49,880
[Thara]

326
00:36:00,727 --> 00:36:02,977
Hey, Yo. Where are you?

327
00:36:02,977 --> 00:36:04,984
Why are you even asking?

328
00:36:04,984 --> 00:36:06,692
I'm in my room.

329
00:36:06,692 --> 00:36:08,932
It's already 8 AM!

330
00:36:22,493 --> 00:36:24,359
Whoa.

331
00:36:24,359 --> 00:36:25,600
You're still young.

332
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,625
Why are you sighing
like you're about to retire?

333
00:36:27,625 --> 00:36:28,762
Let me vent for a bit.

334
00:36:28,762 --> 00:36:31,927
My boyfriend promised
he'd come and intern with me every morning.

335
00:36:31,927 --> 00:36:32,961
Look what happened now.

336
00:36:32,961 --> 00:36:34,427
Time changes, people change.

337
00:36:34,427 --> 00:36:36,320
He's nothing but trouble.

338
00:36:37,932 --> 00:36:40,505
But now you're in trouble, Teacher Thara.

339
00:36:40,505 --> 00:36:41,874
The first class is about to start.

340
00:36:41,874 --> 00:36:43,837
Oh, shit! I have to go.

341
00:36:43,837 --> 00:36:45,677
Alright, bye.

342
00:36:47,263 --> 00:36:51,280
So it's a tie between King and Elsa.

343
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:53,800
[Class Leader Vote]
Come on!

344
00:36:54,072 --> 00:36:57,679
But aren't there 11 of us in this class?

345
00:36:57,679 --> 00:37:00,266
Who hasn't voted?

346
00:37:04,503 --> 00:37:06,967
Mr. Class President.

347
00:37:06,967 --> 00:37:09,417
No, it's Mr. Miang.

348
00:37:09,417 --> 00:37:12,319
You weren't chosen
as class president anymore,

349
00:37:12,319 --> 00:37:15,894
so you don't get to skip voting.

350
00:37:15,894 --> 00:37:17,787
Whoever wants the title can have it!

351
00:37:19,067 --> 00:37:21,888
Hey! You political troublemaker!

352
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:33,070
Take that!

353
00:37:34,172 --> 00:37:36,078
What's going on?

354
00:37:36,078 --> 00:37:37,998
Stop it, kids.

355
00:37:43,941 --> 00:37:45,654
Kids!

356
00:37:45,654 --> 00:37:49,878
You all realize playing like this
is against the school rules, right?

357
00:37:49,878 --> 00:37:52,934
What? But you're late to school,
Teacher Wayo.

358
00:37:52,934 --> 00:37:55,975
Isn't that against the school rules too?

359
00:37:59,358 --> 00:38:00,789
You kids!

360
00:38:00,789 --> 00:38:02,408
I'm gonna deal with you!

361
00:38:02,408 --> 00:38:04,208
Hey!

362
00:38:10,581 --> 00:38:12,975
Hello, Principal Sodchuen.

363
00:38:18,860 --> 00:38:20,411
Teacher Wayo,

364
00:38:20,411 --> 00:38:25,059
if you keep being late like this,
the kids might start copying you.

365
00:38:25,059 --> 00:38:26,532
I'm sorry.

366
00:38:26,532 --> 00:38:29,997
I'm a night owl.

367
00:38:29,997 --> 00:38:31,402
I always wake up late.

368
00:38:31,402 --> 00:38:32,878
What?

369
00:38:32,878 --> 00:38:36,938
You know full well that being a teacher
means you have to wake up early.

370
00:38:36,938 --> 00:38:39,518
So why did you want to be a teacher?

371
00:38:39,518 --> 00:38:44,275
Actually, I just wanted to be close to...

372
00:38:46,010 --> 00:38:47,913
Why are you looking at me?

373
00:38:47,913 --> 00:38:49,920
Don't use me as your excuse.

374
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:52,688
There!

375
00:38:52,688 --> 00:38:54,528
It's obvious.

376
00:39:02,056 --> 00:39:04,584
You're whipped, aren't you?

377
00:39:06,299 --> 00:39:11,217
Oh! This is giving me major déjà vu!

378
00:39:11,217 --> 00:39:14,747
I guess we'll have to get those two to help.

379
00:39:14,747 --> 00:39:15,793
Genius.

380
00:39:15,793 --> 00:39:19,760
Is that what you learned
from being Principal of the Century?

381
00:39:20,863 --> 00:39:25,400
Believe it or not,
Teacher Pobmek used to hate kids so much.

382
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:28,397
Huh? Teacher Pobmek?

383
00:39:28,397 --> 00:39:31,547
But he seems to really like kids.

384
00:39:32,211 --> 00:39:37,040
Do you two know
what made him change his mind?

385
00:39:38,314 --> 00:39:40,283
A salary raise?

386
00:39:40,283 --> 00:39:43,060
You'd need another job for that.

387
00:39:43,060 --> 00:39:46,900
There! I mean the person over there.

388
00:39:46,900 --> 00:39:52,537
♪ Hurt so much my heart's gone numb ♪

389
00:39:52,537 --> 00:39:54,987
- Clap your hands!
- Teacher Solar?

390
00:39:55,592 --> 00:39:57,273
That's right.

391
00:39:57,273 --> 00:40:00,309
If you know why you're doing this job,

392
00:40:00,309 --> 00:40:05,784
you'll find your own value
and be able to do it happily.

393
00:40:05,784 --> 00:40:07,358
Oh, Principal.

394
00:40:07,358 --> 00:40:10,960
You remind me of that day
when my friend gave a speech.

395
00:40:13,185 --> 00:40:15,120
Next,

396
00:40:15,790 --> 00:40:19,061
can we have Teacher Pobmek
come up and say a few words?

397
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:44,520
Well...

398
00:40:47,192 --> 00:40:48,992
Well...

399
00:41:00,155 --> 00:41:05,800
Hello, students and parents.

400
00:41:07,563 --> 00:41:10,840
I'm Teacher Pobmek.

401
00:41:13,051 --> 00:41:14,851
Honestly...

402
00:41:16,051 --> 00:41:18,800
I don't know what to say today.

403
00:41:21,683 --> 00:41:26,400
So I'm just going to tell you a story.

404
00:41:27,848 --> 00:41:29,267
What do we fold this into?

405
00:41:29,267 --> 00:41:32,378
This story is about a man.

406
00:41:32,378 --> 00:41:33,533
Very good!

407
00:41:33,533 --> 00:41:35,219
High-five!

408
00:41:35,219 --> 00:41:37,032
He's a teacher.

409
00:41:37,809 --> 00:41:41,273
But the problem is,
he's not into any of that.

410
00:41:41,273 --> 00:41:44,825
- Good job!
- But he made it through,

411
00:41:44,825 --> 00:41:49,065
thanks to another teacher
who was always there to support him.

412
00:41:51,411 --> 00:41:55,283
Teachers are no different
from their students.

413
00:41:56,465 --> 00:41:59,570
If students are growing and learning,

414
00:41:59,570 --> 00:42:02,880
then teachers are growing and learning too.

415
00:42:09,452 --> 00:42:12,496
And it's a beautiful journey

416
00:42:12,496 --> 00:42:16,778
when you have someone by your side
through it all.

417
00:42:17,843 --> 00:42:20,510
Why is this missing a piece?

418
00:42:22,006 --> 00:42:23,726
Come here!

419
00:42:23,726 --> 00:42:25,546
Give me that!

420
00:42:25,546 --> 00:42:31,360
There are still many obstacles
that can test us at any time,

421
00:42:35,116 --> 00:42:37,255
both from within ourselves

422
00:42:38,591 --> 00:42:40,800
and even from the ones we love.

423
00:42:42,562 --> 00:42:45,140
This story isn't over yet.

424
00:42:45,140 --> 00:42:47,360
It's only just the beginning.

425
00:42:56,853 --> 00:43:00,789
But it made me realize

426
00:43:02,031 --> 00:43:04,280
I truly love being a teacher.

427
00:43:06,505 --> 00:43:07,968
Thank you.

428
00:43:32,412 --> 00:43:33,619
Trust me.

429
00:43:33,619 --> 00:43:37,783
The work you do really matters.

430
00:43:37,783 --> 00:43:40,892
You just have to find the value in it.

431
00:43:40,892 --> 00:43:43,290
That's all.

432
00:44:06,078 --> 00:44:07,878
Solar!

433
00:44:21,443 --> 00:44:22,921
Is something wrong?

434
00:44:24,309 --> 00:44:25,497
No.

435
00:44:25,497 --> 00:44:28,889
I'm just not used to this yet.

436
00:44:28,889 --> 00:44:30,448
We've been together for so long.

437
00:44:30,448 --> 00:44:32,723
It's just holding hands
and you're still not used to it?

438
00:44:32,723 --> 00:44:34,384
That's not it.

439
00:44:34,384 --> 00:44:36,871
I'm used to holding hands.

440
00:44:36,871 --> 00:44:40,520
What I'm still not used to, is this.

441
00:44:54,210 --> 00:44:55,637
Solar!

442
00:45:00,028 --> 00:45:04,092
Teacher Solar is about to propose
to Teacher Pobmek!

443
00:45:10,248 --> 00:45:11,645
No.

444
00:45:14,858 --> 00:45:16,750
- Do it!
- Propose!

445
00:45:16,750 --> 00:45:20,793
Propose!

446
00:45:21,782 --> 00:45:22,993
Alright.

447
00:45:22,993 --> 00:45:25,294
Wait for me here.

448
00:45:25,294 --> 00:45:26,346
I'll be right back.

449
00:45:26,346 --> 00:45:27,710
Wait here.

450
00:45:49,281 --> 00:45:50,759
Teacher Pobmek.

451
00:45:51,558 --> 00:45:52,986
Yes?

452
00:46:08,224 --> 00:46:10,024
Will you marry me?

453
00:46:22,376 --> 00:46:23,892
Of course I will.

454
00:46:42,760 --> 00:47:02,086
Kiss! Kiss!

455
00:47:23,764 --> 00:47:26,247
Come on, Teachers!

456
00:47:26,247 --> 00:47:27,766
Have some guts!

457
00:47:27,766 --> 00:47:30,125
Yeah! You're so Gen Y!

458
00:47:30,125 --> 00:47:31,960
Not Sigma at all!

459
00:48:02,052 --> 00:48:04,050
Even though I'm still not used to it,

460
00:48:05,517 --> 00:48:08,050
I like it better this way.

461
00:48:11,227 --> 00:48:13,901
Yeah. Me too.

462
00:48:46,280 --> 00:48:47,625
Let's go.

463
00:49:01,444 --> 00:49:06,492
And this is the cast of "Love You Teacher"!

464
00:49:13,928 --> 00:49:15,495
He set it up for himself and served himself.

465
00:49:15,495 --> 00:49:17,846
It's really good.

466
00:49:17,846 --> 00:49:19,096
I'm so tired.

467
00:49:19,096 --> 00:49:21,879
- It's so much fun.
- We're not saving any for another take.

468
00:49:21,879 --> 00:49:23,799
My head hurts.

469
00:49:27,135 --> 00:49:30,180
- Mommies, look!
- Is he retying it for you?

470
00:49:32,693 --> 00:49:35,369
Love You Teacher!

471
00:49:35,369 --> 00:49:38,920
Yay!
